ations Development Programme", "Publisher": "United Nations Development Programme", "Type": "Report"}, "hash": "4c8cb66e0f66708db10b5f92a0291c9aeae1218fbe7105e50707e75957161440"}, "2": {"node_id": "547a0b0b-e5c0-46cd-afd2-8e25600884a8", "node_type": null, "metadata": {"Title_URL": "https://www.undp.org/asia-pacific/publications/aphdr-technical-background-paper-2010/08", "Author": "United Nations Development Programme", "Publisher": "United Nations Development Programme", "Type": "Report"}, "hash": "41fd62e10298be636c548aefa237180cf2d22f289e670b5ad014f07a3a59e986"}}, "hash": "528e6e5d5d1229c0aa3ef5b80646c4dad122f4a053e79a5bb9de3534bdfb890f", "text": "Underdeveloped labor markets; lack of legal protection; and class, caste, and gender based discrimination adversely affect women in agriculture in South Asia In Southeast Asia and the Pacific (including China), the 26 key gender issues in agriculture are: gender wage gap, poor working conditions and gender discrimination in agro processing industry. Table 3.6 shows the regional characteristics and key issues of agricultural labor for each of the sub-regions. Table 3.7 Regional Characteristics and Key Issues of Women\u2019s Agricultural Labor Regions Women in agriculture The Key Issues Interventions South Asia Employment to population ratios: Women: 31.4%; men: 78.1% High percentage of informal agricultural labor Higher percentage of women in", "start_char_idx": null, "end_char_idx": null, "text_template": "{metadata_str}\n\n{content}", "metadata_template": "{key}: {value}", "metadata_seperator": "\n"}, "__type__": "1"}, "a7cca0f4-d53e-4d1c-addb-689b522340b2": {"__data__": {"id_": "a7cca0f4-d53e-4d1c-addb-689b522340b2", "embedding": null, "metadata": {"Title_URL": "https://www.undp.org/asia-pacific/publications/aphdr-technical-background-paper-2010/08", "Author": "United Nations Development Programme", "Publisher": "United Nations Development Programme", "Type": "Report"}, "excluded_embed_metadata_keys": [], "excluded_llm